Reasoning: 
1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with controlling the collective behavior of a group of autonomous agents, which falls under the domain of multi-agent systems. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new notion of soft control to intervene in the collective behavior of a distributed system, which is related to systems and control. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper involves designing a control law for a shill agent to synchronize the whole group to an objective heading, which is a problem in artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with controlling the behavior of a group of autonomous agents, which is a problem in robotics. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with a distributed multi-agent model and proposes a method to intervene in the collective behavior of the group, which is related to distributed computing.
